[?1049h[22;0;0t[?1h=MV(1)                        User Commands                       MV(1)[m
[m
[1mNAME[0m[m
       mv - move (rename) files[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mmv [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [[4m-T[24m] [4mSOURCE[24m [4mDEST[0m[m
       [1mmv [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [4mSOURCE[24m... [4mDIRECTORY[0m[m
       [1mmv [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [4m-t[24m [4mDIRECTORY[24m [4mSOURCE[24m...[m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       Rename SOURCE to DEST, or move SOURCE(s) to DIRECTORY.[m
[m
       Mandatory  arguments  to  long  options are mandatory for short[m
       options too.[m
[m
       [1m--backup[22m[=[4mCONTROL[24m][m
              make a backup of each existing destination file[m
[m
       [1m-b     [22mlike [1m--backup [22mbut does not accept an argument[m
[m
       [1m-f[22m, [1m--force[0m[m
              do not prompt before overwriting[m
[m
       [1m-i[22m, [1m--interactive[0m[m
              prompt before overwrite[m
[m
       [1m-n[22m, [1m--no-clobber[0m[m
              do not overwrite an existing file[m
[m
       If you specify more than one of [1m-i[22m, [1m-f[22m, [1m-n[22m, only the final  one[m
       takes effect.[m
[m
       [1m--strip-trailing-slashes[0m[m
              remove any trailing slashes from each SOURCE argument[m
[m
       [1m-S[22m, [1m--suffix[22m=[4mSUFFIX[0m[m
